## Category Card Background — Never Use `--theme-hero-bg` for Card Fills

**Problem:** Using `bg-[var(--theme-hero-bg)]` as the background for category cards makes them invisible. `--theme-hero-bg` is typically white or off-white (the hero section background), and the card text is `text-white` — producing white-on-white.

**Fix:** Use `bg-[var(--theme-shop-button)]` (the accent/action color) for category card backgrounds. It's always a visible, contrasting color that the theme author has already chosen for buttons.

```json
// ❌ BAD — hero-bg is white/off-white; card is invisible
{ "type": "Pressable", "props": { "className": "... bg-[var(--theme-hero-bg)]" },
  "children": [{ "type": "Text", "props": { "className": "text-white" }, "text": "Women" }] }

// ✅ GOOD — shop-button is always a visible accent color
{ "type": "Pressable", "props": { "className": "... bg-[var(--theme-shop-button)] hover:opacity-80" },
  "children": [{ "type": "Text", "props": { "className": "text-[var(--theme-shop-buttonText)]" }, "text": "{{$item.name}}" }] }
```

**Applies to:** Category grid cards, collection tiles, any solid-color card that needs a visible background.

